  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>15 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to make sense of representations of situations involving weights and liquid volumes. Students are reminded that tape diagrams can be used to represent relationships between quantities in different types of problems.</p>
<p>As students analyze descriptions of situations and make connections across representations, they practice looking for and making use of structure (MP7). As they relate the numbers and relationships in situations to those in diagrams, they reason quantitatively and abstractly (MP2). </p>
  </paragraphs>


