<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Estrategias de apoyo para estudiantes con dificultades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="support-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>=== NOT PRESENT ===</p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Display diagram C and situation I.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Cómo saben que este diagrama corresponde a esta situación?</q>  (The 7 in the diagram represents each pack of seeds weighing 7 grams. The 84 shows that all the seed packs weigh 84 grams. The dotted lines in the diagram shows that we don’t know how many seed packs there are.)
      </li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Qué ecuaciones podemos escribir que correspondan a este diagrama?</q>  (<m>{?}\times7=84</m> or <m>84\div7={?}</m>)
      </li>
      <li>Discuss how students know that diagram B and situation E are a match and how the situation could be represented with equations.</li>
      <li>Attend to the language that students use in their explanations, giving them opportunities to describe the situations and diagrams more precisely.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Descripción del desarrollo de lenguaje matemático -->
